	<h2 style="margin-bottom:0px;">High C Performance Management</h2>
	<h1 style="text-align:center; margin-top:0px;">Strengths and Weaknesses</h1>
	<br>
	<h3 style="margin-bottom:5px;">Planning and Goal Setting</h3>
	<table class="with-border" cellpadding="3" ID="Table1">
		<tr>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Strengths</th>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Weaknesses</th>
		</tr>
		<tr valign="top">
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Creates an accurate, believable picture of the future</li>
					<li>Supplies credible details</li>
					<li>Points out that it meets the necessary criteria, thus is the right result</li>
					<li>Convinces of strength of the plan</li>
					<li>Conveys level of expertise that fosters confidence of others in both the leader and the plan</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>May present goal in a colorless, over-formal style</li>
					<li>May offer too many alternatives/combinations of the goal</li>
					<li>May focus too heavily on risks rather than rewards</li>
					<li>Obscures main plan with details</li>
					<li>Tends to focus on negative dimensions of the issue – that is, pitfalls and stumbling blocks</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>
	
	<h3 style="margin-bottom:5px;">Measuring and Monitoring Progress/Coaching</h3>
	<table class="with-border" cellpadding="3" ID="Table2">
		<tr>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Strengths</th>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Weaknesses</th>
		</tr>
		<tr valign="top">
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Demonstrates a clear commitment to excellence</li>
					<li>Lets people know what’s expected</li>
					<li>Impresses followers by personal example</li>
					<li>Convinces through logic and facts</li>
					<li>Clearly lets people know what is expected</li>
					<li>Provides information, guidelines, and procedure</li>
					<li>Explains thought processes; makes thinking visible</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Presents too many details at the expense of the big picture</li>
					<li>Frustrates impatient followers with detail and sequential process to “bottom line”</li>
					<li>Has trouble reading the “audience”</li>
					<li>Offers too many alternatives rather than clear conclusions</li>
					<li>Focuses more on task than people</li>
					<li>Fails to make people feel individually important to the success of the goal</li>
					<li>Discourages contributions “outside the box”</li>
					<li>Quick to point out the inaccuracies or weaknesses of suggestions</li>
					<li>Often doesn’t build rapport with the employee; can come across cool and aloof</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>
	
