	<h2 style="margin-bottom:0px;">High C Performance Management</h2>
	<h1 style="text-align:center; margin-top:0px;">Strengths and Weaknesses</h1>
	<br>
	
	<h3 style="margin-bottom:5px;">Evaluating Performance</h3>
	<table class="with-border" cellpadding="3" ID="Table3">
		<tr>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Strengths</th>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Weaknesses</th>
		</tr>
		<tr valign="top">
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Has everything documented</li>
					<li>Has been drawing conclusions all along; no off-the-cuff judgment</li>
					<li>Stays far and accurate</li>
					<li>Plans meeting with employee carefully with clear objectives</li>
					<li>Shows clearly and specifically where employee met goals and where he/she did not—and by how much</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Will be very strict on evaluation </li>
					<li>Sticks too closely to precedent</li>
					<li>May question and second guess</li>
					<li>Doesn’t encourage a lot of spontaneous, innovative thinking</li>
					<li>Avoids emotions and feelings in evaluating performance</li>
					<li>May miss real issue by focusing on a piece of the puzzle</li>
					<li>Rigid on rules and procedures</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>
	
	<h3 style="margin-bottom:5px;">Conducting Development Review Session/Strategies</h3>
	<table class="with-border" cellpadding="3" ID="Table4">
		<tr>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Strengths</th>
			<th align="left" width="50%">Performance Management Weaknesses</th>
		</tr>
		<tr valign="top">
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Sets example of clear commitment to excellence</li>
					<li>Well-focused on accomplishments</li>
					<li>Motivates through logic and expertise</li>
					<li>Shows people how their work contributes to worthwhile ends</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
			<td>
				<ul>
					<li>Lacks obvious enthusiasm</li>
					<li>Non-demonstrative</li>
					<li>Puts damper on enthusiasm by focusing on negatives</li>
					<li>May be too enthusiastic about pointing out mistakes</li>
					<li>May fail to put employee at ease or build confidence</li>
				</ul>
			</td>
		</tr>
	</table>